# Auto PR after commit (inactive — solo trunk)

**Default workflow:** see `.cursor/rules/solo-trunk-workflow.mdc` — commit on `main`, push to `origin/main`, **no PR**.

Use this file only when the user explicitly asks to open or update a pull request.

## If user requests a PR

1. Follow git safety protocol (status, diff, log, HEREDOC commit message).
2. Push the branch: `git push -u origin HEAD`.
3. Check for an open PR: `gh pr list --head $(git branch --show-current)`.
4. If none exists, create one with `gh pr create` against `main`:
   - Title: concise summary of the branch intent.
   - Body: Summary bullets + Test plan checklist (include `pnpm --filter pawbuck typecheck` when consumer-app changed).
5. Return the **PR URL** when a PR is created or updated.

## Do not

- Force-push unless explicitly requested.
- Open duplicate PRs for the same branch.
- Open PRs automatically when the user only asked to commit/push to trunk.
